{"questionId":"21440","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Sieun hits golf balls into the air. Each time she hits a ball she records <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi></math>, the angle at which&nbsp;the ball is launched into the air, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi></math>, the horizontal distance, in metres, which the ball travels&nbsp;from the point of contact to the first time it lands. The diagram below represents this information.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/3be95eea4a37f38939c4577c8224ca5f9fa56e17.png\"></p>\n<p>Sieun analyses her results and concludes:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>35</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>≤</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>75</mn><mo>°</mo></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine whether the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi></math> against <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi></math> is increasing or decreasing at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>°</mo></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mn>50</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>the curve is decreasing at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> For the final <em><strong>A1</strong></em>, follow through within this question part for their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mn>50</mn></mfenced></math> value. Award <em><strong>A0</strong></em> for an answer of \"decreasing\" with no work shown.</p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21440","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ1.13a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Determine whether the graph of l against θ is increasing or decreasing at θ=50°.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.2—Increasing and decreasing functions","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.5—Integration introduction, areas between curve and x axis"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}